parameters.name: R
parameters.description: Spacecraft range from the Amalthea center of mass in units of radii where RI = 1818 km.

parameters.name: AMALTHEA LATITUDE
parameters.description: Spacecraft Amalthea-centric latitude in units of degrees.

parameters.name: AMALTHEA EAST LONGITUDE
parameters.description: Spacecraft Amalthea-centric east longitude in units of degrees.

parameters.name: PHIO-X
parameters.description: X component of the spacecraft range from the Amalthea center of mass in Amalthea Phi-Omega (PHIO) coordinates. In this coordinate system, X lies in the direction of corotation (at the time of Amalthea closest approach), the X-Z plane planes contains Jupiter's axis of rotation (Omega), and Y completes the right-handed set (towards Jupiter).

parameters.name: PHIO-Y
parameters.description: Y component of the spacecraft range from the Amalthea center of mass in PHIO coordinates (towards Jupiter).

parameters.name: PHIO-Z
parameters.description: Z component of the spacecraft range from the Amalthea center of mass in PHIO coordinates. In this coordinate system, Z is parallel to Jupiter's spin axis (Omega), positive northward.
